verses.text: Again the word of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* came unto me, saying ,
Son of man , cause Jerusalem to know her abominations ,

And say , Thus saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd* unto Jerusalem ; Thy birth and thy nativity \add is\add* of the land of Canaan ; thy father \add was\add* an Amorite , and thy mother an Hittite.\f + \fr 16.3 \ft birth: Heb. cutting out, or, habitation\f*

And \add as for\add* thy nativity , in the day thou wast born thy navel was not cut , neither wast thou washed in water to supple \add thee;\add* thou wast not salted at all , nor swaddled at all.\f + \fr 16.4 \ft to supple…: or, when I looked upon thee\f*
None eye pitied thee, to do any of these unto thee, to have compassion upon thee; but thou wast cast out in the open field , to the lothing of thy person , in the day that thou wast born. \p

¶ And when I passed by thee, and saw thee polluted in thine own blood , I said unto thee \add when thou wast\add* in thy blood , Live ; yea, I said unto thee \add when thou wast\add* in thy blood , Live.\f + \fr 16.6 \ft polluted: or, trodden under foot\f*

I have caused thee to multiply as the bud of the field , and thou hast increased and waxen great , and thou art come to excellent ornaments : \add thy\add* breasts are fashioned , and thine hair is grown , whereas thou \add wast\add* naked and bare.\f + \fr 16.7 \ft caused…: Heb. made thee a million\f*\f + \fr 16.7 \ft excellent…: Heb. ornament of ornaments\f*

Now when I passed by thee, and looked upon thee, behold, thy time \add was\add* the time of love ; and I spread my skirt over thee, and covered thy nakedness : yea, I sware unto thee, and entered into a covenant with thee, saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*, and thou becamest mine.
Then washed I thee with water ; yea, I throughly washed away thy blood from thee, and I anointed thee with oil.\f + \fr 16.9 \ft blood: Heb. bloods\f*
I clothed thee also with broidered work , and shod thee with badgers’ skin , and I girded thee about with fine linen , and I covered thee with silk.
I decked thee also with ornaments , and I put bracelets upon thy hands , and a chain on thy neck.
And I put a jewel on thy forehead , and earrings in thine ears , and a beautiful crown upon thine head.\f + \fr 16.12 \ft forehead: Heb. nose\f*

Thus wast thou decked with gold and silver ; and thy raiment \add was of\add* fine linen , and silk , and broidered work ; thou didst eat fine flour , and honey , and oil : and thou wast exceeding beautiful , and thou didst prosper into a kingdom.
And thy renown went forth among the heathen for thy beauty : for it \add was\add* perfect through my comeliness , which I had put upon thee, saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*. \p
¶ But thou didst trust in thine own beauty , and playedst the harlot because of thy renown , and pouredst out thy fornications on every one that passed by ; his it was.

And of thy garments thou didst take , and deckedst thy high places with divers colours , and playedst the harlot thereupon: \add the like things\add* shall not come , neither shall it be \add so\add*.

Thou hast also taken thy fair jewels of my gold and of my silver , which I had given thee, and madest to thyself images of men , and didst commit whoredom with them,\f + \fr 16.17 \ft of men: Heb. of a male\f*
And tookest thy broidered garments , and coveredst them: and thou hast set mine oil and mine incense before them.

My meat also which I gave thee, fine flour , and oil , and honey , \add wherewith\add* I fed thee, thou hast even set it before them for a sweet savour : and \add thus\add* it was, saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*.\f + \fr 16.19 \ft a sweet…: Heb. a savour of rest\f*

Moreover thou hast taken thy sons and thy daughters , whom thou hast borne unto me, and these hast thou sacrificed unto them to be devoured. \add Is this\add* of thy whoredoms a small matter ,\f + \fr 16.20 \ft to be…: Heb. to devour\f*
That thou hast slain my children , and delivered them to cause them to pass through \add the fire\add* for them?
And in all thine abominations and thy whoredoms thou hast not remembered the days of thy youth , when thou wast naked and bare , \add and\add* wast polluted in thy blood.
And it came to pass after all thy wickedness , ( woe , woe unto thee! saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*;)
\add That\add* thou hast also built unto thee an eminent place , and hast made thee an high place in every street.\f + \fr 16.24 \ft eminent…: or, brothel house\f*
Thou hast built thy high place at every head of the way , and hast made thy beauty to be abhorred , and hast opened thy feet to every one that passed by , and multiplied thy whoredoms.
Thou hast also committed fornication with the Egyptians thy neighbours , great of flesh ; and hast increased thy whoredoms , to provoke me to anger.

Behold, therefore I have stretched out my hand over thee, and have diminished thine ordinary \add food\add*, and delivered thee unto the will of them that hate thee, the daughters of the Philistines , which are ashamed of thy lewd way.\f + \fr 16.27 \ft daughters: or, cities\f*
Thou hast played the whore also with the Assyrians , because thou wast unsatiable ; yea, thou hast played the harlot with them, and yet couldest not be satisfied.
Thou hast moreover multiplied thy fornication in the land of Canaan unto Chaldea ; and yet thou wast not satisfied herewith.
How weak is thine heart , saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*, seeing thou doest all these \add things\add*, the work of an imperious whorish woman ;

In that thou buildest thine eminent place in the head of every way , and makest thine high place in every street ; and hast not been as an harlot , in that thou scornest hire ;\f + \fr 16.31 \ft In that thou buildest…: or, In thy daughters is thine, etc\f*
\add But as\add* a wife that committeth adultery , \add which\add* taketh strangers instead of her husband !
They give gifts to all whores : but thou givest thy gifts to all thy lovers , and hirest them, that they may come unto thee on every side for thy whoredom.\f + \fr 16.33 \ft hirest: Heb. bribest\f*

And the contrary is in thee from \add other\add* women in thy whoredoms , whereas none followeth thee to commit whoredoms : and in that thou givest a reward , and no reward is given unto thee, therefore thou art contrary. \p
¶ Wherefore, O harlot , hear the word of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*:

Thus saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*; Because thy filthiness was poured out , and thy nakedness discovered through thy whoredoms with thy lovers , and with all the idols of thy abominations , and by the blood of thy children , which thou didst give unto them;

Behold, therefore I will gather all thy lovers , with whom thou hast taken pleasure , and all \add them\add* that thou hast loved , with all \add them\add* that thou hast hated ; I will even gather them round about against thee, and will discover thy nakedness unto them, that they may see all thy nakedness.
And I will judge thee, as women that break wedlock and shed blood are judged ; and I will give thee blood in fury and jealousy.\f + \fr 16.38 \ft as: Heb. with judgments of\f*

And I will also give thee into their hand , and they shall throw down thine eminent place , and shall break down thy high places : they shall strip thee also of thy clothes , and shall take thy fair jewels , and leave thee naked and bare.\f + \fr 16.39 \ft thy fair…: Heb. instruments of thine ornament\f*
They shall also bring up a company against thee, and they shall stone thee with stones , and thrust thee through with their swords.

And they shall burn thine houses with fire , and execute judgments upon thee in the sight of many women : and I will cause thee to cease from playing the harlot , and thou also shalt give no hire any more.
So will I make my fury toward thee to rest , and my jealousy shall depart from thee, and I will be quiet , and will be no more angry.

Because thou hast not remembered the days of thy youth , but hast fretted me in all these \add things;\add* behold , therefore I also will recompense thy way upon \add thine\add* head , saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*: and thou shalt not commit this lewdness above all thine abominations. \p
¶ Behold, every one that useth proverbs shall use \add this\add* proverb against thee, saying , As \add is\add* the mother , \add so is\add* her daughter.

Thou \add art\add* thy mother’s daughter , that lotheth her husband and her children ; and thou \add art\add* the sister of thy sisters , which lothed their husbands and their children : your mother \add was\add* an Hittite , and your father an Amorite.

And thine elder sister \add is\add* Samaria , she and her daughters that dwell at thy left hand : and thy younger sister , that dwelleth at thy right hand , \add is\add* Sodom and her daughters.\f + \fr 16.46 \ft thy younger: Heb. lesser than thou\f*

Yet hast thou not walked after their ways , nor done after their abominations : but, as \add if that were\add* a very little \add thing\add*, thou wast corrupted more than they in all thy ways.\f + \fr 16.47 \ft as if…: or, that was lothed as a small thing\f*
\add As\add* I live , saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*, Sodom thy sister hath not done , she nor her daughters , as thou hast done , thou and thy daughters.
Behold, this was the iniquity of thy sister Sodom , pride , fulness of bread , and abundance of idleness was in her and in her daughters , neither did she strengthen the hand of the poor and needy.
And they were haughty , and committed abomination before me: therefore I took them away as I saw \add good\add*.
Neither hath Samaria committed half of thy sins ; but thou hast multiplied thine abominations more than they , and hast justified thy sisters in all thine abominations which thou hast done.

Thou also, which hast judged thy sisters , bear thine own shame for thy sins that thou hast committed more abominable than they : they are more righteous than thou: yea, be thou confounded also, and bear thy shame , in that thou hast justified thy sisters.

When I shall bring again their captivity , the captivity of Sodom and her daughters , and the captivity of Samaria and her daughters , then \add will I bring again\add* the captivity of thy captives in the midst of them:
That thou mayest bear thine own shame , and mayest be confounded in all that thou hast done , in that thou art a comfort unto them.

When thy sisters , Sodom and her daughters , shall return to their former estate , and Samaria and her daughters shall return to their former estate , then thou and thy daughters shall return to your former estate.
For thy sister Sodom was not mentioned by thy mouth in the day of thy pride ,\f + \fr 16.56 \ft mentioned: Heb. for a report, or, hearing\f*\f + \fr 16.56 \ft pride: Heb. prides, or, excellencies\f*

Before thy wickedness was discovered , as at the time of \add thy\add* reproach of the daughters of Syria , and all \add that are\add* round about her, the daughters of the Philistines , which despise thee round about.\f + \fr 16.57 \ft Syria: Heb. Aram\f*\f + \fr 16.57 \ft despise: or, spoil\f*
Thou hast borne thy lewdness and thine abominations , saith the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.\f + \fr 16.58 \ft borne: Heb. borne them\f*
For thus saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*; I will even deal with thee as thou hast done , which hast despised the oath in breaking the covenant. \p
¶ Nevertheless I will remember my covenant with thee in the days of thy youth , and I will establish unto thee an everlasting covenant.
Then thou shalt remember thy ways , and be ashamed , when thou shalt receive thy sisters , thine elder and thy younger : and I will give them unto thee for daughters , but not by thy covenant.
And I will establish my covenant with thee; and thou shalt know that I \add am\add* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*:

That thou mayest remember , and be confounded , and never open thy mouth any more because of thy shame , when I am pacified toward thee for all that thou hast done , saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*.
